ACT III 

INT. HOUSE ENTRANCE HALLWAY — MORNING

WIDE SHOT.

The bags are by the door.

The house looks different in the morning light. Less like a mystery now.

POSY stands at the door.

The staff stands at a respectful distance.

Nobody knows how to do this part.

NORITH hugs him first. Not a polite hug. The kind that means something. POSY startled. Then his hands come up and he holds on.

NORITH
(pulling back)
End of the year. I'm serious.

POSY
I heard you the first time.

NORITH
I'm saying it again for emphasis.

AMRA hugs him next. She pulls back and looks at him through the viewfinder of her camera. Takes a picture.

AMRA
So you can't pretend this didn't happen.

POSY
(small smile)
I wouldn't dare.

MONY extends his hand. POSY shakes it. Then MONY does something that surprises even him. he pulls the old man in by the hand and hug then steps back. Adjusts his bag like nothing happened.

MONY
End of the year.

POSY
I know. Norith said it three times already.

MONY
Not a suggestion.

POSY
I know, Mony.

VICHARA is last. She stands in front of him for a moment. She looks at him the same like day 1 like a business deal. Except this time she's already agreed to it.

She puts her hand on his arm.

VICHARA
Don't make us wait.

POSY covers her hand with his. His hands are slow.

POSY
I won't.

The camera finds VIVOTH standing slightly apart. He has already said his goodbye.

He watches the four of them say goodbye to POSY.

His face is very still.

The car pulls up. Bags go in. Doors close.

The camera stays on POSY standing at the gate as the car moves down the drive. He watches until it turns and disappears.

He stands there a moment longer.

Then he goes back inside.

The gate closes behind him.

CUT TO:

 ONE WEEK LATER 


INT. COFFEE SHOP — MORNING

Two cups on the table.

VICHARA and VIVOTH sit across from each other. It is the first time they have met outside the house. It feels different. 

VICHARA
Have you heard from him?

VIVOTH
He called twice. He sounded fine.

VICHARA
Did he sound like he was going to actually do it?

VIVOTH
He sounded like himself. Which means probably yes and definitely not on anyone else's schedule.

VICHARA
(small exhale)
That man.

VIVOTH
Yeah.

They drink their coffee. The ordinary sounds of the café around them.

VICHARA
Norith asks about you.

VIVOTH
Does he.

VICHARA
He pretends he's asking about the bruise. He's not asking about the bruise.

VIVOTH
(corner of his mouth)
How is it?

VICHARA
Nearly gone.

VIVOTH
Tell him I said he punches like kidergarten bully

VICHARA
I'll tell him you said hi.

VIVOTH
That's not what I said.

VICHARA
I know.

She looks at her cup. Then at him.

VICHARA (CONT'D)
Is everything ok for you?

VIVOTH
(after a pause)
I think so. Ask me again in a few weeks.

She nods. Doesn't push.

They sit in the quiet of two people who went through something together and now figuring out what changed and how to address this.

CUT TO:


INT. SMALL RESTAURANT — AFTERNOON

NORITH, MONY, and AMRA at a corner table. Food between them. The kind of lunch that started as a quick catch-up and has already gone two hours over.

NORITH
I'm just saying. If he calls right on the end of year I win.

MONY
Win what?

NORITH
The moral high ground.

MONY
That's not how moral high ground works.

NORITH
It is how I work.

AMRA is looking at her phone. She has the photographs from the weekend open. Scrolling slowly. The fishing pond. The card table. POSY laughing at something NORITH said. VIVOTH finally sitting inside the circle.

MONY
(noticing)
You've been looking at those since we sat down.

AMRA
I know.

MONY
Are you going to print them?

AMRA
I already did.

She puts her phone down. Picks up her fork.

AMRA (CONT'D)
Do you think about it? What he said. About waiting in that house for forty years.

NORITH
(quieter)
Yeah. I do.

MONY
Dad has that photo. The one he won't let anyone touch. Two boys in a garden.

AMRA
I know.

MONY
I keep looking at it differently now.

A beat.

NORITH
My mom would be so happy.

They both look at him.

NORITH (CONT'D)
I called her after we got back. Just to talk. She was cooking. 

He looks at the table.

NORITH (CONT'D)
I almost said something.

AMRA
Why didn't you?

NORITH
Because he asked us not to. And because I wanted him to have the chance to do it right.

Silence.

MONY
We should call them. Not to say anything. Just checking in.

AMRA nods.

NORITH
Yeah.

They each reach for their phones.


INTERCUT — THREE SEPARATE CALLS

NORITH paces outside the restaurant. His mother picks up on the second ring. Her voice warm and immediate.

AMRA leans against the wall inside. Her father answers. His voice careful the way it always is. 

MONY stands very still at the table. Impatiently listen as his sister speaks.

They all do a small talk first. How are you. How is everything. The ordinary things people say when they mean something else entirely.

And then, almost at the same moment, each of them takes a breath.

They are about to say it.

All four phones light up simultaneously.

A notification. From an unknown estate contact.

They look at their screens.

CLOSE ON AMRA'S PHONE.

Notification lits up her face. Mony looks down at his phone.

She reads it.

The camera holds on her face.

Whatever she expected whatever she thought this week was going to be it wasn't this.

Her father's voice still coming through the phone saying her name.

AMRA
(barely)
Dad. I have to call you back.

She hangs up.

NORITH walks back inside.

They look at each other across the room.

Nobody says anything.

CUT TO BLACK.


EXT. HOUSE — MORNING

WIDE SHOT.

The gate is open. Cars. People moving quietly. The house looks the same. 

VIVOTH stands near the entrance. He got here before anyone else.
 
He is wearing dark clothes and he looks like someone who has had several days to prepare for this and still wasn't ready.

The car pulls up. Four doors open.

VICHARA sees him first. She walks to him without stopping and puts her arms around him. He stands there for a second and then holds on.

NORITH puts a hand on his shoulder when he passes. Doesn't say anything. Doesn't need to.

MONY stops in front of him.

MONY
Are you okay?

VIVOTH
(Nod hesitantly)

MONY
(gives his shoulder a squeeze)

They go inside together.


INT. HOUSE — THE FUNERAL

The sitting room has been arranged. Flowers. Chairs. The light coming through the big windows the way it always did.

The staff. A few people from Posy's life. And the five of them.

The ceremony is quiet and dignified. The camera observes from a respectful distance.

Afterward, the lawyer stands.

THE LAWYER
He left instructions. He asked that this be read here, in this room, to you specifically.

He looks at the four cousins. Then at VIVOTH, and nods once,something separate is coming for him.

He opens the letter.

He looks at MONY.

THE LAWYER (CONT'D)
He asked that you read it.

VICHARA looks up. She wasn't expecting that.

She takes the letter. Unfolds it carefully. Her hands are steady the way they always are. But the camera catches them tighten slightly on the paper.

She reads.

VICHARA
(reading)
"To the four of you."

She pauses. Looks at them once. Then back at the page.

VICHARA (CONT'D)
(reading)
"I have been trying to write this letter for thirty years. Every version I wrote was either too long or too late. So I am going to try to be brief and honest, which Sophea always said I was incapable of."

A small sound in the room. VIVOTH looks at the floor.

VICHARA (CONT'D)
(reading)
"Vichara. You have your mother's eyes and her way of walking into a room like you've already decided what you think of it. She was the most stubborn person I have ever known. You are the second. I mean that as the highest compliment I know how to give."

VICHARA's jaw tightens. She does not look away from the letter.

VICHARA(CONT'D)
(reading)
"Norith. Your mother made this house warm every rainy season. I didn't understand until she left how much of the warmth was her. You walked back into this house and somehow it was warm again. She would be insufferably proud of you. I was too, especially of your cooking."

NORITH makes a sound that is not quite a laugh and not quite a cry. He covers his face briefly with one hand. VICHARA reaches over without looking and puts her hand on his arm.

VICHARA(CONT'D)
(reading)
"Amra. Your father gave me his pen once, a long time ago. I kept it for forty years. I think he knew, even then, that I would need reminding. You found it. He would say that's not a coincidence. He was almost always right."

AMRA has both hands over her mouth. Her shoulders are shaking slightly. MONY glances at her.

VICHARA(CONT'D)
(reading)
"Mony. You asked me if your father was happy when he was young. I told you yes. I want to tell you now what I couldn't say at the table. He was the funniest, most infuriating, most gifted person in this house. He made everything brighter just by being in the room. I fought with him the night before he left and I have regretted every word of it for forty years. If you speak to him and I hope you will tell him the soup is still on the stove. He'll know what that means."

MONY goes still.

VICHARA looks at the page for a moment.

Her face is very controlled. But something behind it has broken open quietly.
She continues.

VICHARA(CONT'D)
(reading)
"I brought you here because I was afraid. I have been afraid for forty years. Afraid the distance was too great with too much time had passed. Afraid that finding you would only show me what I had lost. But you came. You painted badly and cooked surprisingly well and argued at my table and filled this house with noise it hasn't had since your parents were children running in that garden."

He pauses. Just for a breath.

VICHARA(CONT'D)
(reading)
"I want you to tell them. Tell your parents that I have been here. That the house is still standing. The door is open. Amd That I am sorry it took me this long to say so and that if they never forgive me, I understand."

The room is very quiet.

VICHARA(CONT'D)
(reading)
"Thank god I'm dead by the time you read this. I don't want any of you mocking me for my chessy word of choice. Especially The next sentence"

VICHARA(CONT'D)
"I love you to dead"

She folds the letter.

Looks up.

The camera moves slowly across the room. VICHARA, still and composed with tears running down her face. NORITH, not trying to hide anything anymore. MONY's comforting AMRA, her father's camera in her lap, her hand resting on it.

VIVOTH standing slightly apart, the way he always stands.

CUT TO:


INT. HOUSE SITTING ROOM — AFTER THE FUNERAL

The room has emptied. Just the five of them now.

The lawyer approaches VIVOTH quietly and hands him an envelope. Separate from the others. 

VIVOTH takes it. Steps away from the group.

He opens it alone, facing the window. 

He reads it.

The camera stays on his back. We don't see anything yet

But we see his hand come up. Press flat against the window glass.

He stands there for a long moment before he turns the envelope over.

CLOSE ON THE BACK OF THE ENVELOPE.

A photograph slides out.

VIVOTH and POSY. Somewhere in this house. VIVOTH looks young maybe fifteen or sixteen. POSY has his hand on VIVOTH's shoulder. Both of them looking at something outside the frame. Neither looking at the camera.

VIVOTH flips it over.

CLOSE ON POSY'S HANDWRITING.

ENVELOPE
"I leave this house to you because you are probably my favorite. Don't tell them that.
You were the best thing that ever happen to me. You were the one who stayed. I thank your mother not you, son"

VIVOTH looks at it for a long time.

VICHARA appears at his shoulder. She doesn't ask. She just stands next to him.

She looks at it. Then at him.

She doesn't say anything. She just stays there.

After a moment NORITH, then AMARA, then Mony appears on his other side.

All five of them at the window.

Nobody speaks.

The camera pulls back slowly through the glass until they are five small figures standing together in the window of a house that looks, from the outside, like any other house.

FADE TO BLACK.


WEEKS LATER

A series of quiet cuts. No dialogue. Just images.

NORITH on the phone waiting to hear his mom's voice. her voice comes. He is pacing. He stops. He says something. The camera is outside the window...we cannot hear the words. shot of the phone falling from one hand then. cut to norith try to talk into the phone.

AMRA placing a photograph on her father's desk. The one from the sitting room. POSY and his siblings in the garden. She leaves before he comes in. The camera watches him find it. Watches him sit down slowly. Watches him pick it up.

MONY at his father's study door. He knocks. Goes in. Closes the door behind him. The camera stays outside. A long time passes. When the door opens again MONY's eyes are red. 

VICHARA driving. She pulls over. Sits for a moment. It seem like figure is in her passenger seat. She open her mouth then close. then

VICHARA
Mom. I need to tell you something. About a man named Posy.

The camera holds on her face.

Then cuts to black before her mother answers.

FADE OUT.

END OF ACT III.

